#compdef srs_bench
# ============================================================================
# srs_bench - SRS streaming-server benchmark + load-test tool (Go, MIT)
#
# Author : Winlin (winlinvip) + ossrs team
# Upstream: https://github.com/ossrs/srs-bench
#
# srs_bench is the official benchmark for SRS (Simple Realtime Server),
# the popular streaming media server. It generates load against four
# protocol families:
#   - WebRTC SFU (target: SRS WebRTC + WHIP/WHEP)
#   - RTMP / HTTP-FLV / HLS live streaming (target: SRS live)
#   - Janus private protocol (target: Janus Gateway)
#   - GB28181 (target: any GB media server)
#
# The tool spawns N concurrent clients * M streams each, fans them
# against a single endpoint, and reports per-frame statistics
# (FPS / bitrate / jitter / RTT) via an optional stats HTTP endpoint.
#
# The WebRTC lane is built on `github.com/pion/webrtc/v4 v4.1.3`
# (declared verbatim at upstream go.mod HEAD), the canonical Go
# WebRTC stack by the Pion org (github.com/pion/webrtc, 16500+
# stars). pion/webrtc is a from-scratch Go implementation of the
# full WebRTC stack: RTCPeerConnection, RTP / RTCP, DTLS / SRTP /
# SCTP, ICE / STUN / TURN, the SDP offer/answer flow, and the
# data-channel API. It is the parent project that webrtc-rs ported
# to async-Rust (Axis 210 Rust slot).
#
# srs_bench drives concurrent RTCPeerConnections through the SRS
# WebRTC SFU, exercising the publish + subscribe paths under load -
# the canonical "production load test" use case for pion/webrtc.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 210 :: WEBRTC (RTC 1.0 / RFC 8825 + RTP/RTCP/SRTP/DTLS/ICE/SCTP)
# Round 1329 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 210
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : webrtc-rs/webrtc        [R1328 _h26forge]
#   Go      : pion/webrtc             [R1329 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : werift-webrtc           [R1330 closing]
#
# Pion is the ancestor of the lane: pion/webrtc shipped in 2018
# as the first credible pure-language WebRTC stack (no libwebrtc /
# no Chromium). The webrtc-rs project is a port-of-design with
# bidirectional PR cross-flow from pion. werift-webrtc on the
# Node side is similarly pion-influenced. So while the Rust + Node
# clients are clean-room, they trace lineage to the Pion design
# rather than to the Google libwebrtc C++ codebase.
# ============================================================================

_srs_bench() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '-sfu[SFU target server family]:family:(rtc srs live janus gb28181)' \
        '-sr[subscribe URL]:url:' \
        '-pr[publish URL]:url:' \
        '-da[dump audio to file]:file:_files' \
        '-dv[dump video to file]:file:_files' \
        '-pli[PLI request interval in seconds]:seconds:' \
        '-sa[source audio file]:file:_files -g "*.(aac|ogg|opus|mp3)"' \
        '-sv[source video file]:file:_files -g "*.(h264|264|h265|265|webm)"' \
        '-fps[force FPS for source video]:fps:' \
        '-al[enable audio level header extension]:bool:(true false)' \
        '-twcc[enable transport-wide CC for video]:bool:(true false)' \
        '-nn[number of concurrent clients]:n:' \
        '-sn[number of streams per client]:n:' \
        '-delay[client startup stagger delay in ms]:ms:' \
        '-stat[stats HTTP listen address]:address:' \
        '-cap[close connection after publish completes]:bool:(true false)' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
}

_srs_bench "$@"
